{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":926,"text":"We're at a tipping point in human history,"},{"time":3416,"text":"a species poised between gaining the stars\nand losing the planet we call home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9332,"text":"Even in just the past few years,\nwe've greatly expanded"},{"time":12062,"text":"our knowledge of how Earth fits\nwithin the context of our universe."},{"time":16392,"text":"NASA's Kepler mission has discovered"},{"time":19130,"text":"thousands of potential planets\naround other stars,"},{"time":22079,"text":"indicating that Earth is but one\nof billions of planets in our galaxy."},{"time":26273,"text":"Kepler is a space telescope"},{"time":28143,"text":"that measures the subtle dimming of stars\nas planets pass in front of them,"},{"time":32434,"text":"blocking just a little bit\nof that light from reaching us."},{"time":35732,"text":"Kepler's data reveals planets' sizes"},{"time":38332,"text":"as well as their distance\nfrom their parent star."},{"time":41118,"text":"Together, this helps us understand\nwhether these planets are small and rocky,"},{"time":45158,"text":"like the terrestrial planets\nin our own Solar System,"},{"time":47713,"text":"and also how much light they receive\nfrom their parent sun."},{"time":51079,"text":"In turn, this provides clues as to whether\nthese planets that we discover"},{"time":54957,"text":"might be habitable or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57418,"text":"Unfortunately, at the same time\nas we're discovering this treasure trove"},{"time":61481,"text":"of potentially habitable worlds,"},{"time":63594,"text":"our own planet is sagging\nunder the weight of humanity."},{"time":67054,"text":"2014 was the hottest year on record."},{"time":71466,"text":"Glaciers and sea ice that have\nbeen with us for millennia"},{"time":74809,"text":"are now disappearing\nin a matter of decades."},{"time":77944,"text":"These planetary-scale environmental \nchanges that we have set in motion"},{"time":83055,"text":"are rapidly outpacing our ability\nto alter their course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87347,"text":"But I'm not a climate scientist,\nI'm an astronomer."},{"time":91062,"text":"I study planetary habitability\nas influenced by stars"},{"time":94432,"text":"with the hopes of finding\nthe places in the universe"},{"time":96890,"text":"where we might discover\nlife beyond our own planet."},{"time":99862,"text":"You could say that I look for\nchoice alien real estate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103902,"text":"Now, as somebody who is deeply embedded\nin the search for life in the universe,"},{"time":108244,"text":"I can tell you that the more\nyou look for planets like Earth,"},{"time":111611,"text":"the more you appreciate\nour own planet itself."},{"time":115257,"text":"Each one of these new worlds\ninvites a comparison"},{"time":117950,"text":"between the newly discovered planet\nand the planets we know best:"},{"time":121572,"text":"those of our own Solar System."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123662,"text":"Consider our neighbor, Mars."},{"time":125624,"text":"Mars is small and rocky,\nand though it's a bit far from the Sun,"},{"time":129409,"text":"it might be considered\na potentially habitable world"},{"time":131934,"text":"if found by a mission like Kepler."},{"time":133936,"text":"Indeed, it's possible that Mars\nwas habitable in the past,"},{"time":137303,"text":"and in part, this is why\nwe study Mars so much."},{"time":140740,"text":"Our rovers, like Curiosity,\ncrawl across its surface,"},{"time":144130,"text":"scratching for clues as to the origins\nof life as we know it."},{"time":147380,"text":"Orbiters like the MAVEN mission\nsample the Martian atmosphere,"},{"time":150886,"text":"trying to understand how Mars\nmight have lost its past habitability."},{"time":154578,"text":"Private spaceflight companies now offer\nnot just a short trip to near space"},{"time":159143,"text":"but the tantalizing possibility\nof living our lives on Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162844,"text":"But though these Martian vistas"},{"time":164794,"text":"resemble the deserts\nof our own home world,"},{"time":167349,"text":"places that are tied in our imagination\nto ideas about pioneering and frontiers,"},{"time":172921,"text":"compared to Earth"},{"time":174593,"text":"Mars is a pretty terrible place to live."},{"time":177890,"text":"Consider the extent to which\nwe have not colonized"},{"time":181164,"text":"the deserts of our own planet,"},{"time":183068,"text":"places that are lush\nby comparison with Mars."},{"time":185901,"text":"Even in the driest,\nhighest places on Earth,"},{"time":188687,"text":"the air is sweet and thick with oxygen"},{"time":191287,"text":"exhaled from thousands of miles away\nby our rainforests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195374,"text":"I worry -- I worry that this excitement\nabout colonizing Mars and other planets"},{"time":201318,"text":"carries with it a long, dark shadow:"},{"time":204429,"text":"the implication and belief by some"},{"time":206449,"text":"that Mars will be there to save us\nfrom the self-inflicted destruction"},{"time":210002,"text":"of the only truly habitable planet\nwe know of, the Earth."},{"time":214135,"text":"As much as I love\ninterplanetary exploration,"},{"time":216573,"text":"I deeply disagree with this idea."},{"time":218918,"text":"There are many excellent reasons\nto go to Mars,"},{"time":221611,"text":"but for anyone to tell you that Mars\nwill be there to back up humanity"},{"time":225025,"text":"is like the captain of the Titanic\ntelling you that the real party"},{"time":228133,"text":"is happening later on the lifeboats."},{"time":230504,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":233453,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236355,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239142,"text":"But the goals of interplanetary\nexploration and planetary preservation"},{"time":242928,"text":"are not opposed to one another."},{"time":245109,"text":"No, they're in fact two sides\nof the same goal:"},{"time":247640,"text":"to understand, preserve\nand improve life into the future."},{"time":251982,"text":"The extreme environments\nof our own world are alien vistas."},{"time":256045,"text":"They're just closer to home."},{"time":257926,"text":"If we can understand how to create\nand maintain habitable spaces"},{"time":262105,"text":"out of hostile, inhospitable\nspaces here on Earth,"},{"time":265495,"text":"perhaps we can meet the needs\nof both preserving our own environment"},{"time":268932,"text":"and moving beyond it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271161,"text":"I leave you with a final\nthought experiment:"},{"time":273471,"text":"Fermi's paradox."},{"time":275166,"text":"Many years ago, the physicist Enrico Fermi\nasked that, given the fact"},{"time":280028,"text":"that our universe has been around\nfor a very long time"},{"time":282875,"text":"and we expect that there\nare many planets within it,"},{"time":285545,"text":"we should have found evidence\nfor alien life by now."},{"time":288633,"text":"So where are they?"},{"time":290676,"text":"Well, one possible solution\nto Fermi's paradox"},{"time":294043,"text":"is that, as civilizations become\ntechnologically advanced enough"},{"time":297526,"text":"to consider living amongst the stars,"},{"time":299848,"text":"they lose sight of how important it is"},{"time":302332,"text":"to safeguard the home worlds that fostered\nthat advancement to begin with."},{"time":306860,"text":"It is hubris to believe\nthat interplanetary colonization alone"},{"time":311248,"text":"will save us from ourselves,"},{"time":313129,"text":"but planetary preservation\nand interplanetary exploration"},{"time":316658,"text":"can work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318552,"text":"If we truly believe in our ability"},{"time":320675,"text":"to bend the hostile environments of Mars\nfor human habitation,"},{"time":324181,"text":"then we should be able to surmount\nthe far easier task of preserving"},{"time":327767,"text":"the habitability of the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329940,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330996,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}